For example, in my case I have zillions of files I have to see when I do a `git status`, and I live with them. Either I used them in the past, or I am using them, or I am preparing something for the future.
But none of them are to be included in the repository.

pr_body:
Week 3 Report:

  - Created new files: v6ksp.c, v6ksp_driver.cpp, and v6ksp_driver.h.
  - Removed all the changes made last week from ksp.c, ksp_driver.cpp, and ksp_driver.h.
  - Added docqueries for one-to-many, many-to-one, many-to-many, and combinations.
  - Made additional changes in several files to support the functionality of the newly added files.


@pgRouting/admins
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 1228594893, 'comment_body': 'This signature was removed, it has to stay.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 20, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1228595664, 'comment_body': 'You have the function in comments, that is you removed the signature.
Put it back.
You can not remove a signature', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 21, 42, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1228599437, 'comment_body': 'You are overdoing it, with just 2 functions is enough:
See:
https://github.com/pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting/blob/main/sql/dijkstra/_dijkstra.sql#L38
https://github.com/pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting/blob/main/sql/dijkstra/_dijkstra.sql#L63
The one on L28 is used on one to one one to many, many to one and many to many, the one in line 63 is used on combinations
Also, about the function that existed previously that you have to keep, see how it is handled:
https://github.com/pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting/blob/main/sql/dijkstra/_dijkstra.sql#L91', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 26, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1228600877, 'comment_body': 'hmmm, I got mixed up, I placed this comment on the wrong location
anyway, just make sure you only add only two `_pgr_ksp` functions.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 27, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1228601199, 'comment_body': 'and delete none', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 28, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1229025914, 'comment_body': "@cvvergara ma'am here I have created a new driver.h and remove the changes from the old driver.h.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 14, 5, 59, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Aniket-debug', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1229027624, 'comment_body': 'comment out the one-to-one that I created because one-to-one to is already there in older version', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 14, 6, 1, 56, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Aniket-debug', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1229028370, 'comment_body': '@cvvergara New ksp.c the older one would be as it was no changes at all.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 14, 6, 3, 6, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Aniket-debug', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1229029122, 'comment_body': '@cvvergara new driver.cpp older will be as it was again no changes in that one.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 14, 6, 4, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Aniket-debug', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233314630, 'comment_body': 'Reminder: This is okay in the GSoC repository, but needs to be removed when merged to the pgRouting repository.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 21, 5, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233316021, 'comment_body': 'Should be `v4` instead of `v6` I suppose (meaning v4.x.x and onwards).

When we use v4, it means the major version and not the minor version (You might have used v6 to denote v3.6.x, but it will mean v6.x.x).

We use semantic versioning: major.minor.patch
* Major versions: Can have breaking change (aka "deleting" old SQLs)
* Minor versions: Just improvements/additions, no breaking change, e.g. for v3.6 that you are working on.
* Patch: Any bug fixes.

The name v4 will denote that this function will stay on v4 and other older ones can be removed (breaking change).', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 30, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233317283, 'comment_body': "Coding style improvement:
You can do like this:
```
        Edge_t*, size_t,
        II_t_rt*, size_t,
        int64_t*, size_t,
        int64_t*, size_t,
... and similarly
```
It's upto you, but this one looks more compact, also denotes that first `size_t` is for first `Edge_t` and so on.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 34, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233318709, 'comment_body': "You can use this for commenting:
```
/*
... existing code
*/
```

[{'comment_id': 1228594893, 'comment_body': 'This signature was removed, it has to stay.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 20, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1228595664, 'comment_body': 'You have the function in comments, that is you removed the signature.
Put it back.
You can not remove a signature', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 21, 42, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1228599437, 'comment_body': 'You are overdoing it, with just 2 functions is enough:
See:
https://github.com/pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting/blob/main/sql/dijkstra/_dijkstra.sql#L38
https://github.com/pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting/blob/main/sql/dijkstra/_dijkstra.sql#L63
The one on L28 is used on one to one one to many, many to one and many to many, the one in line 63 is used on combinations
Also, about the function that existed previously that you have to keep, see how it is handled:
https://github.com/pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting/blob/main/sql/dijkstra/_dijkstra.sql#L91', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 26, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1228600877, 'comment_body': 'hmmm, I got mixed up, I placed this comment on the wrong location
anyway, just make sure you only add only two `_pgr_ksp` functions.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 27, 55, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1228601199, 'comment_body': 'and delete none', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 13, 19, 28, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'cvvergara', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1229025914, 'comment_body': "@cvvergara ma'am here I have created a new driver.h and remove the changes from the old driver.h.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 14, 5, 59, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Aniket-debug', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1229027624, 'comment_body': 'comment out the one-to-one that I created because one-to-one to is already there in older version', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 14, 6, 1, 56, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Aniket-debug', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1229028370, 'comment_body': '@cvvergara New ksp.c the older one would be as it was no changes at all.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 14, 6, 3, 6, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Aniket-debug', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1229029122, 'comment_body': '@cvvergara new driver.cpp older will be as it was again no changes in that one.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 14, 6, 4, 4, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Aniket-debug', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233314630, 'comment_body': 'Reminder: This is okay in the GSoC repository, but needs to be removed when merged to the pgRouting repository.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 21, 5, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233316021, 'comment_body': 'Should be `v4` instead of `v6` I suppose (meaning v4.x.x and onwards).

When we use v4, it means the major version and not the minor version (You might have used v6 to denote v3.6.x, but it will mean v6.x.x).

We use semantic versioning: major.minor.patch
* Major versions: Can have breaking change (aka "deleting" old SQLs)
* Minor versions: Just improvements/additions, no breaking change, e.g. for v3.6 that you are working on.
* Patch: Any bug fixes.

The name v4 will denote that this function will stay on v4 and other older ones can be removed (breaking change).', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 30, 33, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233317283, 'comment_body': "Coding style improvement:
You can do like this:
```
        Edge_t*, size_t,
        II_t_rt*, size_t,
        int64_t*, size_t,
        int64_t*, size_t,
... and similarly
```
It's upto you, but this one looks more compact, also denotes that first `size_t` is for first `Edge_t` and so on.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 34, 58, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233318709, 'comment_body': "You can use this for commenting:
```
/*
... existing code
*/
```
If it's your code that you added, at the end, it should get deleted (and not commented)", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 42, 46, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233319009, 'comment_body': 'This is GSoC, so it is up to you, but I feel that code is duplicated when creating new files/functions.

It is fine because it might be seeming a bit complicated to you now. We can check this at the end if we have time - if the code looks duplicated and not much complicated, we can consider moving to the same file/function.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 44, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233319203, 'comment_body': "For consistency, let's change this function name to `process` - we have the same name for all the new functions.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 45, 51, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233319492, 'comment_body': "FYI, you can delete/rename/change signatures for the existing C/C++ code if needed. You cannot do so for the older SQL functions.

The idea is `old SQL-new C/C++` case should work the same (or very minor differences) for backward compatibility across minor versions, so old SQL can't be removed and new C/C++ should be written in a way that it works with older SQL too. For new columns that are getting added, we add that in the migration guide.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 47, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233319545, 'comment_body': 'In this file, you need to add the new signatures that you are creating.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 48, 16, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233321468, 'comment_body': "Even for one-to-one, we should have the additional columns for start_vid and end_vid (although they will be the same for all the rows) - that's the plan for this project, the output columns should be consistent.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 18, 14, 59, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1233844766, 'comment_body': 'ok so additional columns have to be added in older SQL. because i cannot create new SQL with same signature(i tried it gives me error that pgr_ksp already exists something like that) ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 19, 10, 13, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Aniket-debug', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1237022284, 'comment_body': "Correct. And that's why the migration is needed for the older function - https://docs.pgrouting.org/latest/en/migration.html (you also need to add in the documentation on how to migrate the old function). We try not to make any breaking API change, but if made, the changes should be very minimal. You can look at `pgr_dijkstra (One to One)` here - earlier it had no `start_vid` or `end_vid` in the output column, then later we added it.

In your case, if the end-user used this query `SELECT colA, colB, ... from your_function` for his/her application, it will have no impact in the new release. But, in case the user used `SELECT * from your_function` in the old release, and the upgrade pgRouting, it can have impact, especially if that query was used inside a function. Hence, we write a migration guide informing the user of the same - `If needed filter out the added columns`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 6, 21, 13, 40, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'krashish8', 'type': 'User'}]

This is a final merge PR containing commits from several different PRs combined. The intermediate PRs made on the [GSoC-pgRouting](https://github.com/pgRouting/GSoC-pgRouting/) repository are as follows: | Description | Pull Requests | | -----------| --------------------- | | pgr_KSP |
